&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Psychological Therapist&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an experienced CAMHS clinician to join BEH and lead the Barnet CAMHS in Specialist Schools team. You will be an experienced Clinical Psychologist, Child and Adolescent Psychotherapist or RMN with strong clinical skills, a proven track record of engaging young people and a willingness to work flexibly and creatively in a school and community setting.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will lead a small and dedicated team, working across 3 educational settings in Barnet and liaising with multi agency partners as well as the CAMHS teams in clinic. You will deliver the assessment and treatment of CYP aged 11-18 years, run groups and drop in clinics and support neurodevelopmental assessments. You will also manage the team and be responsible for delivery against key KPI’s.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like to know more about the role please contact Tina Read, Service Manager or Dr Eleanor Martin on 0208702 4500.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Tina Read&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Service Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: tina.read2@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 0208702 4500&lt;/p&gt;
